    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5,
                                1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 338.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 357, of the 20th ultimo, in
                            relation to the <hi rend="italic">Alliança</hi> incident, was duly
                            received, and I have laid before the President the note of his
                            excellency the minister of state, of the 16th ultimo, conveying the
                            disavowal by His Majesty’s Government of the act of the temporary
                            commander of the <hi rend="italic">Venadito</hi> in firing upon the <hi rend="italic">Alliança</hi> and the assurance that instructions have
                            been sent to Spanish naval commanders in order to avoid the repetition
                            of any such occurrence.</p>
                <p>I am directed by the President to instruct you that, without conceding
                            that the exact location of the <hi rend="italic">Alliança</hi> at the
                            time the shot was fired can be considered a controlling circumstance,
                            this communication of His Majesty’s Government is accepted as a
                            sufficient and satisfactory explanation of the incident.</p>
                <p>You will add an expression of the President’s high appreciation of the
                            friendly tenor of the Duke of Tetuan’s note.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
